reviews.review_text:
Another Sleeper This show is not one would call a show above all shows, none the less, it is another one of those "sleeper shows" that we could never imagine falling into one of the ages, no sir!

After a rough start this amazing show morphs into a whole other world -- thanks to this amazing recording.

Thank you, Rango Keshavan.

Absolutely superb audience recording.  Kudos.

A listener may initially conclude that this is another run-of-the-mill Grateful Dead show, but be forewarned. This is another run-of-the-mill great Grateful Dead performance, all in all, witnessed by this pristine recording.

What lies here is an encouraging testimony to the logical appreciation of technology. The Sony D5 cassette recorder with the complementary EC-220 mics produces an extraordinary recapture of real-logic atmospheric variances. 

A frank appraisal of the essence of melding sound within.

Update to previous review Remember this show...OH TOO WELL>>>>>
music was fine, the sound system a bit questionable with the elements.  Very dusty and windy and the sun was intense!....

All in all a great show, recording here is excellent and very smooth.  It is one of those, you had to be there shows.

I should know...I was Mr. Naked that day....just n case you were wondering......don't drink from anyone's water bottle at a Dead show.....

Good sound considering Taking into consideration how windy these two days were this had arather full sound to it all the same. Rango makes very good recordings in my oppion that is. I was alittle let down at these shows but not now,Listen to Jerry GROWL Run Run Run and see

nice run in ventura 2 days of memorable stuff , this show is great
love china doll .... 
everyone says Jerry to drugged out in the early to mid 80's , maybe ... but most of the ventura shows were special stuff , I think the band really dug playing there .... think of it all the time
Of course,I was there! Thank you tapers,thank you Mr. C.MILLER ! Excellent show,and amazing recording.The wind was fierce this day,with a nip to the air. :} Listen Loud & #dontletgo
